<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1604,2024]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,284,1604,1629]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Discussion.</emphasis>
This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Friese" box="[643,793,1604,1628]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Friese, H. (1903) Neue afrikanische Megachile - Arten II (Hym.). Zeitschrift fur systematische Hymenopterologie und Dipterologie 3, 273 - 290." type="journal article" year="1903">
Friese (
<number box="[727,785,1604,1628]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1903.0">1903</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
from two females from Delagoa Bay, 
<collectingCountry box="[1233,1384,1604,1628]" name="Mozambique" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,237,1640,1664]" name="Angola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Angola</collectingCountry>
. Only the latter has been studied and is here designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[957,1063,1640,1664]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">lectotype</typeStatus>
. It is not the same as 
<emphasis box="[1314,1397,1642,1665]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">sinuata</emphasis>
, as indicated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pasteels" box="[295,467,1676,1700]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refString="Pasteels, J. J. (1965) Revision des Megachilidae (Hymenoptera Apoidea) De L'Afrique Noire. Les Genres Creightoniella, Chalicodoma et Megachile (s. str.). Musee Royal de L'Afrique Centrale - Tervuren, Belgique Annales, Serie In - 8 - Sciences Zoologiques (137), 1 - 563." type="journal article" year="1965">
Pasteels (
<number box="[401,459,1676,1700]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1965.0">1965</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
or 
<taxonomicName box="[505,595,1677,1701]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Creightonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurivilli">
<emphasis box="[505,595,1677,1701]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">aurivilli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as suggested by Baden on a label on the 
<typeStatus box="[1062,1169,1676,1700]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1604,2024]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1712,1737]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female. Vestiture on head mostly black, mesosoma, including legs, mostly white, with black intermixed on scutum, T 
<number box="[384,394,1748,1772]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1.0">1</number>
white; T 
<number box="[499,513,1748,1772]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="2.0">2</number>
white laterally, black mesally; T 
<number box="[890,903,1748,1772]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="3.0">3</number>
orange laterally, black mesally; T 
<number box="[1292,1306,1748,1772]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="4.0">4</number>
–T 
<number box="[1338,1351,1748,1772]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="6.0">6</number>
orange (
<figureCitation box="[159,285,1784,1808]" captionStart="FIGURE 18 a – d" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1572,1595]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1541]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1551]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 18 a – d. Megachile spp. a – b. M. cornigera, female. a. Face. b. Habitus. c – d. M. braunsiana, female. c. Face. d. Habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246143/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[213,241,1784,1808]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="18.0">18</number>
c–d
</figureCitation>
). Lengths: face 
<quantity box="[469,560,1784,1808]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
; scutum 
<quantity box="[662,753,1784,1808]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
; forewing 
<quantity box="[876,967,1784,1808]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="9.5">9.5 mm</quantity>
; body 
<quantity box="[1045,1149,1784,1808]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.27" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" unit="mm" value="12.7">12.7 mm</quantity>
. Structure. Clypeus three times as wide as long, convex and punctuate above, concave and glabrous below, weakly tuberculate ventrolaterally, ventral edge distinctly concave mediolaterally, pointed medially (
<figureCitation box="[932,1027,1856,1880]" captionStart="FIGURE 18 a – d" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1572,1595]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,193,1541]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1551]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 18 a – d. Megachile spp. a – b. M. cornigera, female. a. Face. b. Habitus. c – d. M. braunsiana, female. c. Face. d. Habitus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246143/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[983,1013,1856,1880]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="18.0">18</number>
c
</figureCitation>
); clypeocellus: clypeus 
<number box="[1293,1304,1856,1880]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="1.0">1</number>
: 
<number box="[1308,1352,1856,1880]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="0.5">0.5</number>
; scopal hairs blunt and thickened distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1604,2024]" box="[199,389,1928,1952]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Male. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1436,1604,2024]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1964,1989]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[361,445,1964,1988]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="28.[151,250,1266,1289]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,176,1245]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,175,1246]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 19. Known distribution of Megachile cornigera (black dot), Megachile braunsiana (yellow triangle) and Megachile trichroma (blue square)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/246144/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
Fig. 
<number box="[414,445,1964,1988]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
). In southern Africa this species is known from a few localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[1199,1347,1964,1988]" name="Mozambique" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
and the north-eastern region of 
<collectingCountry box="[414,562,2000,2024]" name="South Africa" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">South Africa</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
